text: Acleris keiferi is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from California and Idaho. Adults have been recorded on wing from May to October.mothphotographersgroup The larvae feed on Rosa californica, Rubus ursinus and Fragaria species.Tortricidae Food Plant Database ==References== Category:Moths described in 1964 keiferi Category:Moths of North America
